author: Gavin Evans
title: Mike Vick Throws Block, Le'Veon Bell Scores Touchdown
text:
This ain't your daddy's Ravens defense. They came into tonight tied for 26th in the NFL in points allowed per game, and they currently trail 13-7 at halftime. The sole touchdown they gave up in the first half was a reverse field score that was sprung by lead blocker, and 35-year-old backup quarterback, Michael Vick .
Ed Reed, Ray Lewis and Tony Siragusa would certainly be turning over in their grave(s). If they were dead.
[via Vine]
